    {"patterns": ["how is an snn different from a regular neural network?", "what is the difference between snns and traditional neural networks?", "how do spiking neural networks compare to anns?", "why are snns different from conventional neural networks?", "what makes snns unique?"], "answer": "Traditional neural networks process continuous numerical values, while SNNs communicate using discrete spikes that occur over time. This allows SNNs to model temporal information and biological neural behavior more naturally.", "difficulty": "intermediate", "learn_more_id": "snn_vs_ann"},
